1 Cucumber
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Garlic Aioli
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
200 g Plant-Based Mince
1 drizzle olive oil
2 tsp honey
tbs honey
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Slice cucumber into thin sticks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook veggie mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add kiwi spice blend and the honey, and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine shredded cabbage mix, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Top each tortilla with cucumber, cabbage and Kiwi spiced pork.
• Drizzle over garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!
ELEVATE ME: If you’ve added extra ingredients to your recipe, dollop over roasted tomato salsa, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and tear over coriander to serve.